oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: TN State Industrial Union Council Bulletin
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Educational bulletin in which one article details the interesting bills coming up in the 74th Tennessee General Assembly. Another hopes the country has a jobs plan ready for after World War II. A third advertises the CIO School at Highlander. The fourth and final article outlines some of the workmen's compensation statutes in the state.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Labor unions--Organizing--United States; Highlander Folk School (Monteagle, Tenn.); Congress of Industrial Organizations (U.S.); Tennessee. General Assembly; Works councils; Labor unions; Labor laws and legislation; Factories; Wages; Wages and labor productivity
